WorkItem.Description:
From doing some tests with the Stopwatch class, I found that it's due to the LayoutTransformControl's constructor. Specifically, it has to do with the code I posted at the bottom of this message.
 
This is a terrible idea having the LayoutTransformControl's template being parsed and loaded *every time the constructor is called* just because someone wants to avoid the generic.xaml for some reason.
 
A quick test of putting the template in the generic.xaml quickly resulted in a speed up of rendering/loading chart controls that use any sort of DisplayAxis.
 
 
The problem code:
 
  // Hard coded template is never meant to be changed and avoids the 
            // need for generic.xaml.
            string templateXaml =
                @"<ControlTemplate " +
                    "xmlns='http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation' " +
                    "xmlns:x='http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml'>" +
                    "<Grid x:Name='LayoutRoot' Background='{TemplateBinding Background}'>" +
                        "<Grid.RenderTransform>" +
                            "<MatrixTransform x:Name='MatrixTransform'/>" +
                        "</Grid.RenderTransform>" +
                    "</Grid>" +
                "</ControlTemplate>";
 
            using (MemoryStream stream = new MemoryStream(Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(templateXaml)))
            {
                Template = (ControlTemplate)XamlReader.Load(stream);
            }
